
# SmartFlowerPot

This is a simple automated plant monitor built with PlatformIO and Arduino.

Features:
- Reads a water level sensor to detect when the reservoir is low.
- Reads a soil wetness sensor to detect when the plant needs watering.
- Controls a pump to water the plant automatically when the soil is dry.
- Displays system status messages on a connected display.

How it works:
- If the water level is below the low threshold, the system shows a refill warning and keeps the pump off.
- If the reservoir has enough water but the soil is dry, it turns the pump on to water the plant.
- If both water level and soil moisture are healthy, it turns the pump off and displays a healthy status.

Usage:
- Build and upload the project with PlatformIO.
- Open the serial monitor at 9600 baud to see water level and wetness readings.

Adjust the threshold values in `src/main.cpp` as needed for your sensors.
        